  "merger_description": "Bertelsmann SE & Co. KGaA (**Bertelsmann**) proposes to merge its music publishing and recording business, Bertelsmann Music Group (**BMG**), with the music publishing and recording business operated under the Concord label and trademark (**Concord**), which is currently majority owned and controlled by Axton Holdings, LLC (**Axton**).\n\nThe proposed merger transaction will involve Bertelsmann and Axton incorporating a new holding company (**New MusicCo**), to which both Bertelsmann \u2013 via subsidiaries comprising BMG \u2013 and Axton via Concord will contribute their respective music recording and publishing businesses (the **Merger**).\n\nBertelsmann is a German multinational media corporation. BMG is the music publishing and music recording division of Bertelsmann. In Australia, BMG acquires rights from songwriters and composers and supplies music publishing services and recorded music products.\n\nConcord is an independent, US-based music publishing and recording company supporting artists globally. In Australia, Concord supplies music publishing services and recorded music products.",
